Sinopec Kantons Holdings Limited Announces Audited Consolidated Cash Flows Results for the Year Ended December 31, 2016
Apr 10 17
Sinopec Kantons Holdings Limited announced audited consolidated cash flows results for the year ended December 31, 2016. For the year, net cash generated from operating activities was HKD 590,578,000 against HKD 1,475,146,000 a year ago. Purchase of property, plant and equipment was HKD 143,850,000 against HKD 313,207,000 a year ago.


Sinopec Kantons Holdings Limited Proposes Final Dividend for the Year Ended December 31, 2016, Payable on June 30, 2017; Reports Audited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Year Ended December 31, 2016
Mar 30 17
The Board of Sinopec Kantons Holdings Limited recommended a dividend of HKD 0.070 per share payable in cash for the whole year of 2016 compared to HKD 0.050 per share paid in 2015, excluding the interim dividend of HKD 0.035 per share in cash for 2016 paid on October 18, 2016 compared to HKD 0.025 per share paid in 2015, the final dividend of HKD 0.035 per share in cash for 2016 will be paid to all the shareholders whose names appear in the register of the members of the company on 30 June 2017. A final dividend in respect of the year ended December 31, 2016 of 3.5 HK cents per share, amounting to a total dividend of HKD 87,016,000 is to be proposed at the annual general meeting to be held on June 13, 2017. 

The company reported audited consolidated earnings results for the year ended December 31, 2016. For the year, the company reported revenue of HKD 1,766,590,000 against HKD 2,043,630,000 a year ago. Operating profit was HKD 553,961,000 against HKD 730,373,000 a year ago. Profit before income tax was HKD 1,140,303,000 against HKD 1,218,648,000 a year ago. Profit for the year was HKD 1,004,986,000 compared to HKD 1,026,918,000 a year ago. Profit attributable to equity holders of the company was HKD 1,005,259,000 against HKD 1,026,852,000 a year ago. Basic and diluted earnings per share for profit attributable to equity holders of the company were 40.43 cents against 41.30 cents a year ago. Capital expenditures was HKD 281,206,000 compared to HKD 313,207,000 a year ago. The decrease in revenue was mainly due to a significant decrease in natural gas pipeline transmission volume of Yu Ji Pipeline Company in Shandong Province under the short-term oversupply in the natural gas market of Shandong Province in 2016.


Sinopec Kantons Holdings Limited, Annual General Meeting, Jun 13, 2017
Mar 30 17
Sinopec Kantons Holdings Limited, Annual General Meeting, Jun 13, 2017, at 10:00 China Standard Time. Location: Taishan Room (Level 5), Island Shangri-La Pacific Place, Supreme Court Road Central Hong Kong Agenda: To receive, consider and adopt the audited consolidated financial statements and the reports of the directors and auditors of the company for the year ended 31 December 2016; to approve and declare a final dividend for the year ended 31 December 2016; to re-elect Mr. Chen Bo as an executive Director; to re-elect Mr. Ye Zhijun as an executive Director; to re-elect Ms. Tam Wai Chu, Maria as an independent non-executive Director; to re-elect Dr. Wong Yau Kar, David as an independent non-executive Director; to authorize the board of Directors to fix the Directors' remuneration; to re-appoint Messrs PricewaterhouseCoopers as auditors of the company and authorize the Board to fix their remuneration; to grant a general mandate to the Directors to issue new shares; to grant a general mandate to the Directors to repurchase shares; and to extend the general mandate granted to the Directors to issue new shares.


